---
import logo from "../assets/energy-plus-logo.png";
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="container site-footer__inner">
    <div class="site-footer__brand">
      <span class="footer-lockup">
        <img class="footer-lockup__logo" src={logo.src} width="104" height="30" alt="Energy Plus" />
        <span class="footer-lockup__div" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="wordmark__industry">Supermarkets</span>
      </span>
      <p class="site-footer__line">
        Independent energy partner to supermarkets. We don't sell the box. We diagnose
        the store and verify the savings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <nav class="site-footer__nav" aria-label="Footer">
      <a href="#problem">The problem</a>
      <a href="#procurement">The engineer</a>
      <a href="#what-we-find">What we find</a>
      <a href="#proof">Proof</a>
      <a href="#calculator">Calculator</a>
      <a href="#book">Apply Now</a>
    </nav>
  </div>

  <div class="container" id="disclaimers">
    <p class="site-footer__legal">
      <strong>How to read this page.</strong> Energy Plus is an independent
      energy solutions partner. We do not manufacture equipment. We diagnose
      each property and procure, size, and integrate the right technologies
      from our stack for that specific building. The numbered notes below apply
      to the marked figures and statements throughout this page.
    </p>
    <ol class="site-footer__notes">
      <li id="disc-results">
        <strong>1. Savings and performance figures.</strong> All savings,
        bill-reduction, equipment-life, maintenance, and payback figures shown
        (including ranges such as 20&ndash;40% and 8&ndash;14%) are illustrative
        estimates or results achieved at specific facilities under their own
        conditions. They are not predictions or guarantees of your results.
        Case studies reflect results with specific technologies we deploy. Your
        actual results depend on your building, climate, occupancy, equipment
        condition, and utility rates, which is exactly why we measure your floor
        at your meter before you commit. Modeled numbers are directional
        estimates, not quotes.
      </li>
      <li id="disc-terms">
        <strong>2. Program terms and eligibility.</strong> Our done-for-you
        program, including negotiation, pricing, and contract terms, is offered
        case-by-case and depends on factors such as the number of facilities in
        your portfolio and the size of your electricity bills. Properties that
        do not qualify for the done-for-you program may instead be offered
        self-directed ("do-it-yourself") options, which carry different terms,
        pricing, and responsibilities. "No cost," "the diagnosis is on us," and
        "nothing owed" describe the diagnosis and pilot phase for qualifying
        properties; they do not describe the cost of any installed solution.
        Eligibility, scheduling, and availability are determined during the
        application and diagnosis process.
      </li>
      <li id="disc-tax">
        <strong>3. Tax incentives.</strong> Section 179D and any tax figures
        are potential amounts based on current federal rules and assumptions;
        they are not tax advice. Actual deductions depend on your building, the
        work performed, and your tax situation. Consult a qualified tax advisor.
      </li>
      <li id="disc-utility">
        <strong>4. Utility and incentive programs.</strong> Utility-program
        coverage (for example, "up to 75%," or the state percentages shown in
        the calculator) varies by state, utility, and program, and is subject to
        program availability, funding, and qualification. Amounts shown are
        illustrative and are not guaranteed.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="container site-footer__meta">
    <span>&copy; {year} Energy Plus</span>
    <span class="site-footer__neutral">Independent Energy Solutions Partner.</span>
  </div>
</footer>

<style>
  .site-footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg-header);
    padding-block: var(--space-xl) var(--space-l);
  }
  .site-footer__inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-l);
  }
  .site-footer__brand {
    max-width: 34ch;
  }
  .footer-lockup {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.7rem;
  }
  .footer-lockup__logo {
    height: 26px;
    width: auto;
    display: block;
  }
  .footer-lockup__div {
    width: 1px;
    height: 20px;
    background: var(--line-strong);
  }
  .wordmark__industry {
    font-family: "Oswald", var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .site-footer__line {
    margin-top: var(--space-s);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .site-footer__nav {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.65rem;
    align-content: start;
  }
  .site-footer__nav a {
    color: var(--body);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    transition: color 0.25s ease;
  }
  .site-footer__nav a:hover {
    color: var(--gold-text);
  }
  .site-footer__legal {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 78ch;
  }
  .site-footer__legal strong {
    color: var(--body);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .site-footer__notes {
    margin: var(--space-m) 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-s);
    max-width: 78ch;
  }
  .site-footer__notes li {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--muted);
    /* a target highlight when an in-page marker jumps here */
    scroll-margin-top: 5rem;
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }
  .site-footer__notes li:target {
    color: var(--body);
  }
  .site-footer__notes strong {
    color: var(--body);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .site-footer__meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-s);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-m);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
</style>
